Bit.Name: EN_DE_PWM
Bit.Description: Diode-Emulation Enable -> 0: diode-emulation disabled; 1: diode-emulation enabled.

Bit.Name: EN_BUCK
Bit.Description: Phase 1/2 Analog Bias Enable -> 0: bias for the analog circuitry is disabled; 1: bias for the analog circuitry is enabled.

Bit.Name: EN_PWM
Bit.Description: Phase 1/2 Enable -> 0: PWM operation is disabled, the buck can't switch; 1: PWM operation is enabled and the buck can start switching.

Bit.Name: EN_CP
Bit.Description: Charge-Pump Enable -> 0: CP disabled; 1: CP enabled.

Bit.Name: BUCKEN
Bit.Description: This bit stores the value of the internal enable status -> 0: Buck disabled; 1: Buck enabled.

Bit.Name: OverTemp
Bit.Description: Over-Temp Status Latch -> 0: no over-temp event; 1: an over-temp event is detected.

Bit.Name: ValleyCLVP2
Bit.Description: Phase 2 Valley Current Limit Latch -> 0: no valley current-limit event has taken place; 1: the valley-current limit has been tripped and this value is latched.

Bit.Name: ValleyCLVP1
Bit.Description: Phase 1 Valley Current Limit Latch -> 0: no valley current-limit event has taken place; 1: the valley-current limit has been tripped and this value is latched.

Bit.Name: OverCurrentS
Bit.Description: Phase 1/2 Secondary Current Limit Latch -> 0: no secondary current limit event has been detected in either phase 1 or phase 2; 1: the secondary current limit has been tripped in one of the phases and this value is latched.

Bit.Name: OverCurrentP2
Bit.Description: Phase 2 Current Limit Latch -> 0: no current-limit event has taken place in Phase 2; 1: the primary current limit has been tripped in Phase 2 and this value is latched.

Bit.Name: OverCurrentP1
Bit.Description: Phase 1 Current Limit Latch -> 0: no current-limit event has taken place in Phase 1; 1: the primary current limit has been tripped in Phase 1 and this value is latched.

Bit.Name: OTP_READ_DONE
Bit.Description: OTP Read-Done -> 0: the internal OTP hasn't been read-in yet; 1: the internal OTP has been read.

Bit.Name: OverTempNOW
Bit.Description: Over-Temp Status -> 0: no over-temp event; 1: an over-temp event is detected.

Bit.Name: ValleyCLVP2NOW
Bit.Description: Phase 2 Valley Current Limit Status -> 0: no valley current-limit event is detected at the moment; 1: at the moment the valley-current limit is tripped.

Bit.Name: ValleyCLVP1NOW
Bit.Description: Phase 1 Valley Current Limit Status -> 0: no valley current-limit event is detected at the moment; 1: at the moment the valley-current limit is tripped.

Bit.Name: OverCurrentSNOW
Bit.Description: Phase 1/2 Secondary Current Limit Status -> 0: no secondary current limit event is detected at the moment in either phase 1 or phase 2; 1: a secondary current limit is tripped in one of the phases at the moment.

Bit.Name: OverCurrentP2NOW
Bit.Description: Phase 2 Current Limit Status -> 0: no current-limit event is detected in Phase 2 at the moment; 1: the primary current limit is tripped in Phase 2 at the moment.

Bit.Name: OverCurrentP1NOW
Bit.Description: Phase 1 Current Limit Latch -> 0: no current-limit event is detected in Phase 1 at the moment; 1: the primary current limit is tripped in Phase 1 at the moment.

Bit.Name: Set_iSLP_3
Bit.Description:
These bits set the inductor value to be used for slope-compensation.
0000: 220nH
0001: 330nH
0010: 470nH
0011: 560nH
0100: 680nH
0101: 820nH
0110: 1000nH
0111: 1200nH
1000: 1500nH
1001: 2200nH
other: ILLEGAL
